<body>

<div class="container">
    <h1>The Essential Guide to Keyword Density Checking for SEO Success</h1>

    <p>Are you looking to improve your content's ranking on Google? One of the fundamental aspects of on-page SEO is striking the right balance with your keyword usage. That’s where a reliable Keyword Density Checker comes in handy.</p>

    <h2>What is Keyword Density and Why is it Important?</h2>
    <p>Keyword density is simply the percentage of times a specific keyword or phrase appears in your text compared to the total word count. Finding the right balance is crucial:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Too Low:</strong> Search engines might not fully understand what your content is about, leading to a lower ranking.</li>
        <li><strong>Too High:</strong> This is known as "keyword stuffing," a practice that can hurt your search rankings and make your content sound unnatural to readers.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Introducing Our Free Keyword Density Checker Tool</h2>
    <p>We've created a simple and effective tool to help you with this task. It’s designed to give you a clear, quick analysis of your content.</p>

    <blockquote>
        <strong>Keyword Density Checker:</strong> Paste your text to analyze the frequency and density of single, two, and three-word keywords. This helps you optimize content for SEO by ensuring you're not over- or under-using important terms.
    </blockquote>

    <h3>How to Use the Tool for Best Results</h3>
    <ol>
